article.headline: Pascarelli's 16 lead Marist past Niagara 63-62
article.description: — Josh Pascarelli scored 16 points including the game winner with two seconds left and Marist beat Niagara 63-62 on Saturday.
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- — Josh Pascarelli scored 16 points including the game winner with two seconds left and Marist beat Niagara 63-62 on Saturday. Pascarelli shot 7 for 11, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc for the Red Foxes (17-12, 12-8 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Jackson Price scored 13 points while shooting 4 for 9 (1 for 5 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line and added five rebounds. The Purple Eagles (15-15, 11-9) were led in scoring by Quandre Bullock, who finished with 19 points. Braxton Bayless added 13 points for Niagara. Kwane Marble II finished with 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
